                <head>2. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>General Lansdale visited Vietnam from January 2 to 14, 1961. On January 17, he
                    reported on his trip in a memorandum to Secretary of Defense Gates,
                    recommending: “The U.S. should recognize that Vietnam is in a critical condition
                    and should treat it as a combat area of the cold war, as an area requiring
                    emergency treatment.” For text of the memorandum, see <hi rend="italic">United
                        States-Vietnam Relations, 1945-1967</hi>, Book 11, pages 1-12.</p>
            </div>
